ls0 ws0">Notice Peter&apos;s description of the same spiritual building.<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m343 x82 h4 y1567 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1 Peter 2:5-8. How many similarities do you find here to what<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m65c x82 h4 ydb5 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul wrote to the Ephesians? If every Christian becomes in<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m2ae x82 h4 yea6 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">a sense a priest, must he have an offering? Heb. 8:3. Compare<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m1306 x82 h4 y1e0b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rev. 20 : 6. </div><div class="t m2df x84 h4 y109e ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This figure of speech by which individual church members<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m5e6 x82 h4 y209b ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are thought of as being parts of a building occurs also in Ps.<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t m7aa x82 h4 y1143 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">144:12, where sons are spoken of as plants and daughters as<span class="fc0 sc0"> </span></div><div class="t mea6 x82 h4 y136f ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">cornerstones. </div><div class="t m221 x26 h71 y135f ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">THINK IT THROUGH </div><div class="t m5 x9b h71 y1542 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m2ed x8b h71 y135f ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What kind of stone am I in the temple of the Lord? </div><div class="t m103c x14 h6 yeb1 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;How amazed is Heaven at the pres-</div><div class="t m155d x11 h6 y1607 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ent condition of the church that could </div><div class="t mc54 x17 h6 yde6 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be so much to the world if every stone </div><div class="t mc02 x17 h6 y1d3e ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">were in its proper place, a living stone </div><div class="t m2d13 x17 h6 y142d ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to emit light! </div><div class="t m61b x2c h35 y142d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A </div><div class=